divs: Sighting DetailsI walked my girlfriend to her car around 9:40 pm and looked up and saw what I thought at first was 2 lines of flying geese, one behind the other. i realized that it was moving too fast to be geese even though the lights seemed to be above cloud level. there were several waves of these strings of lights, some brighter than others. traveling perpendicular to the direction of the clouds' movement and visible through the clouds. my girlfriend also witnessed this. the event lasted about 10 min. each line of lights disappeared after about 10 seconds as it flew northward and was drowned out by the lights of Springfield. i called the springfield Police to see if stange lights had been reported flying over Springfield, and the officer checked with the dispatcher and told me there had been no other reports of lights. I gave the officer a brief description of what I saw and she told me to call back if i saw anything else.
Summary: several long strings of dull lights, like flying wings.
